a near-native, silky smooth scrolling and interaction experience on mobile devices.","titles":[]},"1":{"title":"Core Features","content":"Physics Simulation Engine — Frame-rate normalized via Delta Time, eliminating speed differences across any screen refresh rate for consistent inertia feel. Includes inertia protection: if the finger pauses for more than 80ms before release, velocity is automatically cleared to prevent unintended scrollingAxis Locking — Automatically determines gesture intent at the start of each touch, filters diagonal jitter, and locks the gesture to a single axis (horizontal or vertical) for the entire durationSmart Edge Detection — Automatically yields control back to the browser when scrolling reaches boundaries, compatible with iOS swipe-back and other native behaviorsEmergency Stop Click Protection — Distinguishes between \"user wants to click\" and \"user wants to brake\". Only blocks click events during high-speed inertia scrolling to prevent accidental tapsMulti-finger Tracking & Lock — Locks the active finger via Touch ID to prevent coordinate jumps during multi-finger alternation. When multiple fingers are detected, the engine goes completely silent and hands control to the browser for native gestures (pinch-to-zoom, etc.)UI Library Presets — Built-in preset configurations for Element Plus, Ant Design Vue, Naive UI, VxeTable, Arco Design, PrimeVue, and VuetifyHybrid Device Lazy Hijacking — Four-state machine (dormant/standby/pending-active/active): zero intrusion on pure PC, on-demand hijacking for hybrid devices (Surface / touchscreen laptops), with a pending-active intermediate state to eliminate accidental activationCSS Rotation Coordinate Transform — Supports CSS transform: rotate() landscape scenarios by applying inverse coordinate transforms via discrete angle axis-swapping, with zero trigonometric overheadZero Dependencies — Pure native implementation, no extra dependencies needed","titles":["Introduction"]},"2":{"title":"What Problems It Solves","content":"The Vue ecosystem still lacks mobile Table solutions that can stand alongside mainstream desktop table stacks. For complex flows such as reporting, mobile also needs high-performance tables with full interaction capabilities, but that gap remains obvious today. In practice teams usually take one of two paths: build a table in-house, where touch interaction, scrolling mechanics, and advanced features are extremely expensive to implement and maintain; or reuse desktop-oriented stacks such as Element Plus tables, which are not optimized for mobile and often feel wrong on touch and small screens. When reusing desktop table components on mobile, common pain points include: Diagonal Swipe Accidental Touch — horizontal data scanning unintentionally triggers vertical page scrolling due to imprecise finger pathsUnstable Directional Locking — slight finger tilt causes frequent axis switching and a shaky scroll pathSluggish Touch Response — native overflow: auto often lags in deeply nested UI structuresLack of Natural Momentum — scrolling stops too abruptly or feels stiff after release, requiring repeated swipesVisual Header Tearing — fixed headers fail to keep pixel-level sync with body scrollingInconsistent Cross-Device Haptics — refresh-rate differences produce inconsistent inertia feel across devicesGesture Logic Conflicts — multi-finger coordinate jumps or interference with native gestures such as iOS swipe-backHybrid Device Interference — aggressive hijacking on Surface/touch laptops can hurt mouse and trackpad usersCSS Rotation Coordinate Mismatch — transform: rotate() landscape layouts misalign physical touch direction and logical scroll direction v-mobile-table addresses these by intercepting touch flow and running an in-directive scroll physics engine; see How It Works for the full breakdown.","titles":["Introduction"]},"3":{"title":"How It Works","content":"The directive intercepts touch event flow and runs a complete in-directive scroll physics pipeline, including axis decision, velocity sampling, inertia decay, edge yielding, and hybrid-device strategies for stable mobile behavior. Read How It Works for the full mechanism breakdown and implementation details.","titles":["Introduction"]},"4":{"title":"Use Cases","content":"","titles":["Introduction"]},"5":{"title":"Data viewing","content":"Complex mobile data views such as wide tables, financial reports, and reconciliation sheets. You need horizontal dragging, vertical browsing, sorting, and nested tables within a small viewport, which demands strong table capabilities, touch feel, and rendering performance.","titles":["Introduction","Use Cases"]},"6":{"title":"Cross-platform consistency","content":"The same business screens must work on both desktop and mobile, delivering predictable interaction without rewriting table business logic.","titles":["Introduction","Use Cases"]},"7":{"title":"Next Steps","content":"Follow the Usage Guide for installation through advanced optionsRead How It Works for mechanism details and design rationaleLearn about Landscape Mode for CSS rotation supportBrowse Examples for real-world use cases","titles":["Introduction"]},"8":{"title":"Usage Guide","content":"This page covers common usage patterns for the v-mobile-table directive. For complete configuration options and type definitions, see API.","titles":[]},"9":{"title":"Installation","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"10":{"title":"Global Registration","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"11":{"title":"Local Registration","content":"If you don't need global registration, you can import the directive directly in a component:","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"12":{"title":"Usage in Templates","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"13":{"title":"Using UI Library Presets","content":"For UI libraries with built-in presets, simply pass the preset name — no need to manually find scroll container selectors: For the full list of supported presets and their selectors, see API — TablePreset.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"14":{"title":"Using Custom Selectors","content":"For UI libraries without built-in presets, use selector to specify the scroll container inside the table: selector takes priority over preset. If both are provided, the element specified by selector will be used. If neither is provided, the directive's bound element itself is used as the scroll container.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"15":{"title":"Custom Physics Parameters","content":"Adjust friction and drag threshold based on your use case:","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"16":{"title":"Dynamic Control","content":"Pass false to completely disable the directive — all event listeners and style hijacking will be fully cleaned up: You can also use the enabled property, which has the same effect: enabled: false and passing false to the directive are equivalent — both fully destroy the directive instance (removing all event listeners and restoring original styles). You do not need to use this for device detection; the directive's mode: 'auto' handles that automatically.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"17":{"title":"Device Detection Mode","content":"By default, the directive uses mode: 'auto' which automatically detects the device type and applies the optimal strategy: Desktop (pure PC): Dormant — no event binding, zero overheadMobile (phone/tablet): Immediately activate full touch handlingHybrid (Surface / touchscreen laptop): Lazy hijacking — only activates after confirming a real touch drag, avoiding interference with mouse/trackpad users Use mode: 'always' to force-enable touch handling regardless of device type. This is useful for debugging or when you know the target environment: In most cases, mode: 'auto' (the default) is the recommended choice. Only use 'always' when you have a specific reason to bypass device detection.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"18":{"title":"Disabling Edge Detection","content":"By default, the directive detects when scrolling reaches the container boundary and hands control back to the browser, enabling native gestures like iOS swipe-back. In fullscreen overlay scenarios (e.g. landscape mode), this is undesirable. Set disableEdgeDetection: true to keep full control: Only enable this when the table is inside a fullscreen overlay or a context where browser-native edge gestures should be suppressed. In normal page layouts, edge detection improves UX by allowing swipe-back and outer scroll.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"19":{"title":"CSS Rotation Support","content":"When using CSS transform: rotate() to simulate landscape mode on mobile, the touch coordinate axes no longer align with the element's logical axes. The rotation parameter tells the directive to apply an inverse coordinate transform: Supported values: 0 (default), 90, -90, 180. For a complete landscape toggle example, see the Landscape Mode guide.","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"20":{"title":"Lifecycle Callbacks","content":"","titles":["Usage Guide"]},"21":{"title":"Options & Types","content":"Option tables, TypeScript types, and library exports for Vue3 Mobile Table. A Vue 3 custom directive that adds touch scroll support to table elements. In templates, use the v-mobile-table attribute. For global registration and local import, see the Usage Guide.","titles":[]},"22":{"title":"Type Definitions","content":"","titles":["Options & Types"]},"23":{"title":"MobileTableOptions","content":"Configuration options interface for the directive. PropertyTypeDefaultDescriptionenabledbooleantrueWhether to enable the directive. When false, all event listeners and style hijacking are fully cleaned up (equivalent to passing false to the directive)presetTablePreset-UI library preset name, automatically applies the corresponding scroll container selectorselectorstring-CSS selector for the target scroll element, takes priority over presetfrictionnumber0.95Friction/decay rate. Higher = slower decay (smoother scrolling), lower = faster stop (range: 0.8 - 0.99)dragThresholdnumber5Displacement threshold (px) before determining scroll direction, distinguishes minor jitter from intentional draggingdisableInertiabooleanfalseWhether to disable inertia scrolling. When true, scrolling stops immediately on finger releaseclickBlockThresholdnumber0.5Speed threshold (px/ms) for emergency stop click blocking. Higher = more lenient, lower = more strict (range: 0.3 - 1.0)mode'auto' | 'always''auto'Device detection mode. 'auto': automatic detection with lazy hijacking for hybrid devices. 'always': always activate touch handling regardless of device typerotation0 | 90 | -90 | 1800CSS rotation angle (degrees). When the container uses CSS transform: rotate() to simulate landscape mode, the directive applies an inverse transform to touch coordinates for correct scroll mappingdisableEdgeDetectionbooleanfalseWhether to disable edge detection. When true, the directive will not hand control back to the browser when scrolling reaches the boundary. Useful for fullscreen overlays where native gestures (e.g. iOS swipe-back) are unwantedonScrollStart() => void-Callback fired when scrolling starts, after finger displacement exceeds dragThreshold and direction is lockedonScrollEnd() => void-Callback fired when scrolling ends, after inertia animation fully stops Scroll container priority: selector > preset > the directive's bound element. Full Type Signature:","titles":["Options & Types","Type Definitions"]},"24":{"title":"TablePreset","content":"Supported UI library preset types and their corresponding scroll container selectors. PresetUI LibrarySelector'element-plus'Element Plus.el-scrollbar__wrap'ant-design-vue'Ant Design Vue.ant-table-body'arco-design'Arco Design.arco-table-body'naive-ui'Naive UI.n-scrollbar-container'primevue'PrimeVue.p-datatable-table-container'vuetify'Vuetify.v-table__wrapper tbody'vxe-table'VxeTable.vxe-table--body-inner-wrapper","titles":["Options & Types","Type Definitions"]},"25":{"title":"DeviceType","content":"Device type detected by the directive's internal detection logic. ValueDescription'mobile'Pure mobile device (phone/tablet) with coarse pointer + touch capability'desktop'Pure desktop without touch capability'hybrid'Hybrid device (Surface / touchscreen laptop) with touch but fine pointer","titles":["Options & Types","Type Definitions"]},"26":{"title":"HijackState","content":"Internal state machine for lazy hijacking on hybrid devices. StateDescription'dormant'Pure desktop, no-op'standby'Hybrid device default, only sentinel events attached'pending-active'After touchstart, coordinates recorded but styles not hijacked yet'active'Styles hijacked, full touch event binding active","titles":["Options & Types","Type Definitions"]},"27":{"title":"Exports","content":"","titles":["Options & Types"]},"28":{"title":"UI_LIBRARY_SELECTORS","content":"UI library selector preset mapping constant.","titles":["Options & Types","Exports"]},"29":{"title":"getSelectorByPreset","content":"Get the corresponding CSS selector by preset name. Parameters ParameterTypeDescriptionpresetTablePresetUI library preset name Returns string | undefined — The corresponding CSS selector, or undefined if the preset does not exist.","titles":["Options & Types","Exports"]},"30":{"title":"detectDeviceType","content":"Detects the current device type based on touch capability and pointer characteristics. Returns DeviceType — The detected device type.","titles":["Options & Types","Exports"]},"31":{"title":"Internal Physics Engine Parameters","content":"Physics engine constants used internally by the directive (not externally configurable): ConstantValueDescriptionDEFAULT_FRICTION0.95Default friction/decay rateMIN_VELOCITY0.05Velocity threshold (px/ms) to stop inertia animationMAX_DT32Max frame interval limit (ms), prevents jumps after frame dropsDEFAULT_DRAG_THRESHOLD5Default drag detection threshold (px)INERTIA_STOP_DELAY80Inertia protection delay (ms). If finger pauses longer than this before release, inertia is not triggeredSAFE_CLICK_VELOCITY0.5Default speed threshold (px/ms) for emergency stop click blocking","titles":["Options & Types"]},"32":{"title":"Element Plus","content":"Using Vue3 Mobile Table with Element Plus tables","titles":[]},"33":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"34":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"35":{"title":"Ant Design Vue","content":"Using Vue3 Mobile Table with Ant Design Vue tables","titles":[]},"36":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"37":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"38":{"title":"Naive UI","content":"Using Vue3 Mobile Table with Naive UI tables","titles":[]},"39":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"40":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"41":{"title":"VxeTable","content":"Using Vue3 Mobile Table with VxeTable","titles":[]},"42":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"43":{"title":"Basic Usage","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"44":{"title":"Other Libraries","content":"Using Vue3 Mobile Table with other UI libraries or custom tables","titles":[]},"45":{"title":"Other UI Libraries","content":"Vue3 Mobile Table supports Table components from all desktop Vue UI component libraries. For libraries with built-in presets, see API and use preset for quick integration.","titles":["Other Libraries"]},"46":{"title":"Arco Design Vue","content":"","titles":["Other Libraries","Other UI Libraries"]},"47":{"title":"Vuetify","content":"","titles":["Other Libraries","Other UI Libraries"]},"48":{"title":"PrimeVue","content":"","titles":["Other Libraries","Other UI Libraries"]},"49":{"title":"All Available Presets","content":"PresetUI LibraryScroll Container Selector'element-plus'Element Plus.el-scrollbar__wrap'ant-design-vue'Ant Design Vue.ant-table-body'naive-ui'Naive UI.n-scrollbar-container'vxe-table'VxeTable.vxe-table--body-inner-wrapper'arco-design'Arco Design.arco-table-body'primevue'PrimeVue.p-datatable-table-container'vuetify'Vuetify.v-table__wrapper tbody","titles":["Other Libraries"]},"50":{"title":"No Preset? Use Selector","content":"For libraries without built-in presets, use selector to specify the actual scrollable container element inside the table. You'll need to use browser DevTools to find the CSS selector for the DOM element responsible for scrolling: If you'd like to add built-in preset support for a UI library, feel free to submit an Issue or PR on GitHub.","titles":["Other Libraries"]},"51":{"title":"Landscape Mode","content":"Many PC-oriented table components have a large number of columns. When viewed on a mobile device in portrait orientation, the horizontal space is insufficient, and users must scroll extensively to see all the data. Rotating to landscape orientation effectively swaps the screen's width and height, providing a much wider viewport for table content.","titles":[]},"52":{"title":"Why CSS transform: rotate() Instead of Alternatives?","content":"There are several ways to achieve a landscape layout on mobile, but each has significant trade-offs: ApproachDrawbackscreen.orientation.lock('landscape')Requires the page to be in fullscreen mode first (Element.requestFullscreen()). Most browsers reject the lock outside of fullscreen or user-initiated events, and iOS Safari does not support it at allForce users to rotate the deviceRelies on the user's physical action and the device's auto-rotate setting. Cannot be triggered programmatically, and many users keep rotation lock enabledResponsive redesignRequires completely redesigning the table layout for narrow screens — high cost, and may not suit data-dense tables that inherently need many columns CSS transform: rotate(90deg) avoids all of the above problems: Works on all browsers and all devices — no API restrictions, no permission promptsIs purely programmatic — triggered by a button tap, no reliance on device orientationPreserves the original table layout — no need to redesign columns or break the PC table structureHas zero runtime cost — GPU-composited transform, no reflow or repaint The only downside is that after CSS rotation, the physical touch axes and the element's logical scroll axes become misaligned. That is exactly what the rotation parameter in v-mobile-table solves — it automatically applies an inverse coordinate transform to correct the touch mapping.","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"53":{"title":"How It Works","content":"Use CSS transform: rotate(90deg) to rotate the table containerSwap width and height (width: 100vh, height: 100vw) so the rotated container fills the screenSet rotation: 90 on the directive — internally, transformCoords() maps touch coordinates (clientX, clientY) to (clientY, -clientX), aligning scroll direction with the rotated table's logical axes","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"54":{"title":"Configuration","content":"The rotation parameter accepts the following values: ValueDescription0No rotation (default)90Container rotated 90° clockwise-90Container rotated 90° counter-clockwise180Container rotated 180°","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"55":{"title":"Live Demo","content":"This example needs to be experienced on a mobile device. Click the button to enter the full-screen landscape mode.","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"56":{"title":"Transform Origin","content":"The combination of transform-origin: top left and translate: 100vw 0 is the key positioning technique. After rotating 90° clockwise around the top-left corner, the container shifts off-screen to the left. The translate: 100vw 0 pushes it back, making it cover the entire viewport precisely.","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"57":{"title":"Notes","content":"","titles":["Landscape Mode"]},"58":{"title":"Disable Edge Detection in Landscape Mode","content":"In landscape mode, it's recommended to set disableEdgeDetection to true. The main reason is that while horizontally browsing wide tables, gestures frequently reach the screen edges. If edge detection remains enabled, gestures may be released at the boundary and trigger native system events (such as back navigation gestures). Disabling edge detection keeps control within the table scroll logic and helps prevent accidental system-level actions. If you toggle landscape by state, you can also write it explicitly:","titles":["Landscape Mode","Notes"]},"59":{"title":"Safe Area Insets","content":"On devices with notches or rounded corners (e.g., iPhone), apply safe-area padding directly to the landscape container:","titles":["Landscape Mode","Notes"]},"60":{"title":"Responsive Sizing","content":"When your project uses a framework with built-in responsive font scaling (e.g., font size automatically increases on larger screens), rotating to landscape mode triggers this scaling. However, if table column widths are fixed in pixels, they won't scale proportionally, causing column headers to wrap or content to overflow. Example scenario: Portrait mode: font-size = 14px, column width = 100px (looks balanced)Landscape mode: font-size = 18px (auto-scaled), column width = 100px (unchanged) → header text wraps Solution: Use a helper function that calculates column width based on both viewport width and a maximum constraint: Apply the vw() function to your table column widths: This approach ensures that as the viewport (and font size) grows, column widths scale proportionally, maintaining visual balance across all screen sizes.","titles":["Landscape Mode","Notes"]},"61":{"title":"How It Works","content":"v-mobile-table intercepts touch event flow and implements a complete in-directive scroll physics engine, covering gesture direction decision, velocity sampling, inertia decay, edge yielding, and device-specific strategies so desktop table components stay stable and follow-finger on mobile.","titles":[]},"62":{"title":"Axis Locking","content":"Automatically determines gesture intent when displacement exceeds the threshold, then locks the gesture to a single axis for its entire duration:","titles":["How It Works"]},"63":{"title":"Touch History Queue","content":"Uses sliding window sampling instead of traditional weighted averages, keeping only touch points from the last 50ms to calculate release velocity. This fundamentally eliminates sampling jitter on low-end devices and over-dense sampling on high refresh rate screens:","titles":["How It Works"]},"64":{"title":"Frame Rate Normalization","content":"Physics decay during inertia is normalized via Delta Time, ensuring the same swipe produces identical scroll distances regardless of screen refresh rate:","titles":["How It Works"]},"65":{"title":"Synchronous Event Dispatching","content":"Combined with dirty value detection, proactively dispatches scroll events to force immediate header synchronization, solving the visual tearing caused by asynchronous native scroll events:","titles":["How It Works"]},"66":{"title":"Edge Detection","content":"Automatically yields control when scrolling reaches container boundaries, including detection for both horizontal and vertical axes and scenarios where no scroll is needed:","titles":["How It Works"]},"67":{"title":"Hybrid Device Lazy Hijacking","content":"Uses a four-state machine to handle mixed environments — pure PC stays dormant, mobile activates immediately, and hybrid devices use sentinel events that only trigger full hijacking after confirming a real touch drag:","titles":["How It Works"]},"68":{"title":"Home","content":"Vue3 Mobile Tablevue3-mobile-table is a lightweight interaction engine specifically designed to adapt Vue desktop table components for mobile devices. With perfect compatibility for major UI libraries like Element Plus, Ant Design Vue, and VxeTable, it allows you to grant your PC tables native-grade, buttery-smooth mobile interaction experiences with just a single line of code.","titles":[]},"69":{"title":"介绍","content":"vue3-mobile-table 是一个轻量级解决方案，专门用于弥合桌面表格组件与移动端触摸交互之间的体验差距。通过一个简单的指令，它可以让任何 Vue PC 表格组件（ 例如：Element Plus、Ant Design Vue、Naive UI 等UI库中的 Table 组件）在移动设备上也能获得接近原生级、丝滑流畅的滚动与交互体验。","titles":[]},"70":{"title":"核心特性","content":"物理仿真引擎 — 基于 Delta Time 的帧率归一化，消除任意刷新率屏幕之间的速度差异，提供一致的惯性体感。内置惯性保护：手指停顿超过 80ms 再松开时自动清零速度，防止误触发惯性滚动方向轴锁定 — 在每次触摸开始时自动判定手势意图，过滤对角线抖动，整个手势期间只锁定在一个轴向（横向或纵向）智能边缘感知 — 滚动触达边界时自动交还控制权给浏览器，兼容 iOS 侧滑返回等原生行为急停点击保护 — 区分\"用户想点击\"与\"用户想刹车\"，仅在高速惯性滚动时拦截点击事件，防止误触多指追踪与锁定 — 通过 Touch ID 追踪锁定活跃手指，防止多指交替导致的坐标跳变。检测到多指时引擎完全静默，将控制权交还浏览器处理原生手势（如缩放）UI 库预设 — 内置 Element Plus、Ant Design Vue、Naive UI、VxeTable、Arco Design、PrimeVue、Vuetify 等主流 UI 库的预设配置混合设备懒接管 — 四态状态机（dormant/standby/pending-active/active）：纯 PC 零侵入，混合设备（Surface / 触屏笔记本）按需劫持，通过 pending-active 中间态消除误触激活CSS 旋转坐标逆变换 — 支持 CSS transform: rotate() 横屏场景，通过离散角度轴交换自动矫正触摸坐标，零三角函数开销零依赖 — 纯原生实现，无需额外依赖","titles":["介绍"]},"71":{"title":"解决了什么问题","content":"Vue 生态中尚未出现可对标主流桌面表格栈的移动端 Table 方案。在报表等复杂业务场景下，移动端同样需要具备高性能与完整交互能力的表格组件，但当前生态存在明显空缺。 实际落地通常只有两种路径：其一，自研表格组件，但触控交互、滚动机制与复杂功能实现成本极高，开发与维护负担沉重；其二，复用 Element Plus 等桌面端表格组件，但由于未针对移动端优化，在触控与小屏场景下普遍存在体验问题。 复用桌面表格时，常见痛点包括： 对角线滑动误触 — 用户本想横向查看表格数据，却因手指路径不直而意外触发页面纵向滚动，导致视线丢失滚动方向不纯粹 — 手指轻微倾斜就可能在横纵轴之间频繁切换，滑动路径显得杂乱滚动不跟手 — 在复杂 UI 组件嵌套场景中，原生 overflow: auto 常出现明显滞后缺少惯性反馈 — 松手后滚动立即中断或惯性生硬，远距离浏览需要反复拖拽表头滚动撕裂 — 表体滚动时固定表头无法像素级同步，出现错位或延迟不同设备体感差异 — 刷新率差异导致同一套代码在不同设备上手感不一致手势冲突 — 多指操作坐标跳变，或边界处干扰 iOS 侧滑返回等系统手势混合设备干扰 — 在 Surface、触屏笔记本等设备上盲目劫持会影响鼠标与触控板使用CSS 旋转横屏坐标错乱 — transform: rotate() 场景下触摸物理方向与逻辑滚动方向错位 v-mobile-table 通过接管触摸事件流，在指令内以滚动物理引擎应对上述问题；实现细节见 工作原理。","titles":["介绍"]},"72":{"title":"工作原理","content":"该指令通过接管触摸事件流，在内部实现方向判定、速度采样、惯性衰减、边缘交还与混合设备策略等完整滚动物理机制，保证移动端滚动既跟手又稳定。 你可以在 工作原理 中查看完整机制说明与关键实现思路。","titles":["介绍"]},"73":{"title":"适用场景","content":"","titles":["介绍"]},"74":{"title":"数据查看","content":"面向移动端的宽表、财务报表、对账清单等复杂数据展示场景。需要在有限屏幕内支持横向拖拽、纵向浏览、排序及嵌套表等多维交互，对表格功能、触控体验与渲染性能要求较高。","titles":["介绍","适用场景"]},"75":{"title":"跨端一致体验","content":"同一业务页面需同时覆盖 PC 与移动端，在不重写表格业务逻辑的前提下，实现一致且可预期的交互体验。","titles":["介绍","适用场景"]},"76":{"title":"下一步","content":"跟随 使用指南 从安装到高级选项完成配置阅读 工作原理 了解滚动机制与设计思路了解 移动端横屏方案 的 CSS 旋转支持浏览 示例 查看实际使用案例","titles":["介绍"]},"77":{"title":"使用指南","content":"本页介绍 v-mobile-table 指令的常见用法。完整的配置项和类型定义请参考 API。","titles":[]},"78":{"title":"安装","content":"","titles":["使用指南"]},"79":{"title":"全局注册","content":"","titles":["使用指南"]},"80":{"title":"局部注册","content":"如果不需要全局注册，可以在组件中直接导入指令：","titles":["使用指南"]},"81":{"title":"在模板中使用","content":"","titles":["使用指南"]},"82":{"title":"使用 UI 库预设","content":"对于已内置预设的 UI 库，直接传入 preset 即可，无需手动查找滚动容器选择器： 支持的预设列表和对应选择器请查看 API — TablePreset。","titles":["使用指南"]},"83":{"title":"使用自定义选择器","content":"对于没有内置预设的 UI 库，通过 selector 指定表格内部的滚动容器： selector 的优先级高于 preset。如果两者同时提供，将使用 selector 指定的元素。如果都未提供，则默认使用绑定指令的元素本身。","titles":["使用指南"]},"84":{"title":"自定义物理参数","content":"根据使用场景调整摩擦力和拖拽阈值：","titles":["使用指南"]},"85":{"title":"动态控制","content":"传入 false 可完全禁用指令——所有事件监听和样式劫持都会被彻底清理： 也可以通过 enabled 属性控制，效果完全一致： enabled: false 与传 false 等价——两者都会完全销毁指令实例（移除所有事件监听并还原原始样式）。你不需要用它来做设备判断，指令的 mode: 'auto' 已经自动处理了设备检测。","titles":["使用指南"]},"86":{"title":"设备检测模式","content":"默认情况下，指令使用 mode: 'auto' 自动检测设备类型并采用最优策略： 纯 PC：休眠状态 — 不绑定任何事件，零开销纯移动端（手机/平板）：立即激活完整触摸处理混合设备（Surface / 触屏笔记本）：懒接管 — 仅在确认真实触摸拖拽后才激活，避免对鼠标/触控板用户造成干扰 使用 mode: 'always' 可强制启用触摸处理，忽略设备类型。适用于调试或明确知道目标环境的场景： 大多数场景下，推荐使用 mode: 'auto'（默认值）。仅在有明确需求绕过设备检测时才使用 'always'。","titles":["使用指南"]},"87":{"title":"禁用边缘检测","content":"默认情况下，指令会在滚动触达容器边界时将控制权交还浏览器，以支持 iOS 侧滑返回等原生手势。在全屏覆盖层场景（如横屏模式）下，这个行为是不需要的。设置 disableEdgeDetection: true 可保持指令的完全接管： 仅在表格处于全屏覆盖层或需要阻止浏览器原生边缘手势的场景下启用此选项。在常规页面布局中，边缘检测能提升用户体验（允许侧滑返回和外层滚动）。","titles":["使用指南"]},"88":{"title":"CSS 旋转支持","content":"当通过 CSS transform: rotate() 模拟移动端横屏时，触摸坐标轴与元素逻辑轴不再对齐。rotation 参数会告知指令当前旋转角度，自动执行坐标逆变换： 支持的值：0（默认）、90、-90、180。完整的横屏切换示例请查看移动端横屏方案。","titles":["使用指南"]},"89":{"title":"生命周期回调","content":"","titles":["使用指南"]},"90":{"title":"配置项与类型","content":"Vue3 Mobile Table 的选项表、TypeScript 类型与库导出说明。 Vue 3 自定义指令，为表格元素添加触摸滚动支持。在模板中使用 v-mobile-table 属性。全局注册与局部导入见使用指南。","titles":[]},"91":{"title":"类型定义","content":"","titles":["配置项与类型"]},"92":{"title":"MobileTableOptions","content":"指令的配置选项接口。 属性类型默认值说明enabledbooleantrue是否启用指令。设为 false 时将完全销毁实例（清理事件监听 + 还原样式），等价于 v-mobile-table=\"false\"presetTablePreset-UI 库预设名称，自动应用对应 UI 库的滚动容器选择器selectorstring-目标滚动元素的 CSS 选择器，优先级高于 presetfrictionnumber0.95摩擦力/衰减率，值越大衰减越慢（滚动越丝滑），值越小即停感越强（建议范围：0.8 - 0.99）dragThresholdnumber5判定滚动方向前的位移阈值 (px)，用于区分轻微抖动点击和有意识的拖拽disableInertiabooleanfalse是否禁用惯性滚动，为 true 时手指松开即停止clickBlockThresholdnumber0.5急停点击拦截的速度阈值 (px/ms)，值越大越宽松，值越小越严格（建议范围：0.3 - 1.0）mode'auto' | 'always''auto'设备检测模式。'auto'：自动检测，混合设备启用懒接管。'always'：始终激活触摸处理，忽略设备类型rotation0 | 90 | -90 | 1800CSS 旋转角度（度数）。当容器通过 CSS transform: rotate() 模拟横屏时，指令会对触摸坐标进行逆变换以正确映射滚动方向disableEdgeDetectionbooleanfalse是否禁用边缘检测。为 true 时，滚动到达边界后不会交还控制权给浏览器，始终由指令接管。适用于全屏覆盖层等不希望触发浏览器原生手势（如 iOS 侧滑返回）的场景onScrollStart() => void-滚动开始回调，在用户手指位移超过 dragThreshold 并锁定方向后触发onScrollEnd() => void-滚动结束回调，在惯性动画完全停止后触发 滚动容器定位优先级：selector > preset > 指令绑定的元素本身。 完整类型签名：","titles":["配置项与类型","类型定义"]},"93":{"title":"TablePreset","content":"支持的 UI 库预设类型及对应的滚动容器选择器。 预设值对应 UI 库选择器'element-plus'Element Plus.el-scrollbar__wrap'ant-design-vue'Ant Design Vue.ant-table-body'arco-design'Arco Design.arco-table-body'naive-ui'Naive UI.n-scrollbar-container'primevue'PrimeVue.p-datatable-table-container'vuetify'Vuetify.v-table__wrapper tbody'vxe-table'VxeTable.vxe-table--body-inner-wrapper","titles":["配置项与类型","类型定义"]},"94":{"title":"DeviceType","content":"指令内部设备检测逻辑识别的设备类型。 值说明'mobile'纯移动端（手机/平板），粗指针 + 触摸能力'desktop'纯 PC，无触摸能力'hybrid'混合设备（Surface / 触屏笔记本），有触摸但主指针为精细指针","titles":["配置项与类型","类型定义"]},"95":{"title":"HijackState","content":"混合设备懒接管的内部状态机。 状态说明'dormant'休眠，纯 PC 设备，不做任何操作'standby'待命，混合设备默认状态，仅挂哨兵事件'pending-active'待确认激活，touchstart 后记录坐标但不劫持样式'active'激活，劫持样式并绑定全套触摸事件","titles":["配置项与类型","类型定义"]},"96":{"title":"导出","content":"","titles":["配置项与类型"]},"97":{"title":"UI_LIBRARY_SELECTORS","content":"UI 库选择器预设映射表常量。","titles":["配置项与类型","导出"]},"98":{"title":"getSelectorByPreset","content":"根据预设名称获取对应的 CSS 选择器。 参数 参数类型说明presetTablePresetUI 库预设名称 返回值 string | undefined — 对应的 CSS 选择器，如果预设不存在则返回 undefined。","titles":["配置项与类型","导出"]},"99":{"title":"detectDeviceType","content":"检测当前设备类型，基于触摸能力和指针特性进行判断。 返回值 DeviceType — 检测到的设备类型。","titles":["配置项与类型","导出"]},"100":{"title":"内部物理引擎参数","content":"指令内部使用的物理引擎常量（不可外部配置）： 常量值说明DEFAULT_FRICTION0.95默认摩擦力/衰减率MIN_VELOCITY0.05停止惯性动画的速度阈值 (px/ms)MAX_DT32最大帧间隔限制 (ms)，防止掉帧后产生跳变DEFAULT_DRAG_THRESHOLD5默认拖拽判定阈值 (px)INERTIA_STOP_DELAY80惯性保护延迟 (ms)，手指停顿超过此时间再松开则不触发惯性SAFE_CLICK_VELOCITY0.5急停点击拦截的默认速度阈值 (px/ms)","titles":["配置项与类型"]},"101":{"title":"Element Plus","content":"在 Element Plus 表格中使用 Vue3 Mobile Table","titles":[]},"102":{"title":"在线演示","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"103":{"title":"基础用法","content":"","titles":["Element Plus"]},"104":{"title":"Ant Design Vue","content":"在 Ant Design Vue 表格中使用 Vue3 Mobile Table","titles":[]},"105":{"title":"在线演示","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"106":{"title":"基础用法","content":"","titles":["Ant Design Vue"]},"107":{"title":"Naive UI","content":"在 Naive UI 表格中使用 Vue3 Mobile Table","titles":[]},"108":{"title":"在线演示","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"109":{"title":"基础用法","content":"","titles":["Naive UI"]},"110":{"title":"VxeTable","content":"在 VxeTable 表格中使用 Vue3 Mobile Table","titles":[]},"111":{"title":"在线演示","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"112":{"title":"基础用法","content":"","titles":["VxeTable"]},"113":{"title":"其他库","content":"Vue3 Mobile Table 支持所有桌面端 Vue3 UI 组件库中的 Table 组件。 已内置预设的组件库请参阅 API，使用 preset 即可快速接入。","titles":[]},"114":{"title":"Arco Design Vue","content":"","titles":["其他库"]},"115":{"title":"Vuetify","content":"","titles":["其他库"]},"116":{"title":"PrimeVue","content":"","titles":["其他库"]},"117":{"title":"所有可用预设","content":"预设名UI 库滚动容器选择器'element-plus'Element Plus.el-scrollbar__wrap'ant-design-vue'Ant Design Vue.ant-table-body'naive-ui'Naive UI.n-scrollbar-container'vxe-table'VxeTable.vxe-table--body-inner-wrapper'arco-design'Arco Design.arco-table-body'primevue'PrimeVue.p-datatable-table-container'vuetify'Vuetify.v-table__wrapper tbody","titles":["其他库"]},"118":{"title":"没有预设？使用 Selector","content":"对于没有内置预设的组件库，可以通过 selector 指定表格内部实际可滚动的容器元素。你需要通过浏览器开发者工具找到该表格组件中负责滚动的 DOM 元素的 CSS 选择器： 如果你希望为某个组件库添加内置预设支持，欢迎在 GitHub 上提交 Issue 或 PR。","titles":["其他库"]},"119":{"title":"移动端横屏方案","content":"许多 PC 端表格组件拥有大量列字段。在移动端竖屏模式下，横向空间严重不足，用户需要频繁横向滑动才能查看完整数据。旋转到横屏方向可以有效地交换屏幕的宽高，为表格内容提供更宽的视口。","titles":[]},"120":{"title":"为什么选择 CSS transform: rotate() 方案？","content":"实现移动端横屏有多种方式，但每种都有明显的局限性： 方案缺陷screen.orientation.lock('landscape')需要页面先进入全屏模式（Element.requestFullscreen()）。大多数浏览器在非全屏或非用户手势触发时会拒绝锁定，且 iOS Safari 完全不支持此 API强制用户旋转设备依赖用户的物理操作和设备的自动旋转设置，无法通过代码触发，且许多用户会锁定屏幕方向响应式重新设计需要为窄屏完全重新设计表格布局——成本高昂，且对于天然需要多列的数据密集型表格并不适用 CSS transform: rotate(90deg) 规避了上述所有问题： 全浏览器、全设备兼容 — 无 API 限制，无权限弹窗纯代码可控 — 通过按钮点击触发，不依赖设备方向保留原始表格布局 — 无需重新设计列结构，PC 端表格原样复用零运行时开销 — GPU 合成层变换，不触发重排或重绘 唯一的副作用是 CSS 旋转后，触摸的物理轴向与元素的逻辑滚动轴向不再对齐。这正是 v-mobile-table 的 rotation 参数所解决的——它会自动对触摸坐标进行逆变换矫正，使滑动方向与旋转后的表格逻辑方向一致。","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"121":{"title":"工作原理","content":"使用 CSS transform: rotate(90deg) 旋转表格容器交换宽高（width: 100vh，height: 100vw），使旋转后的容器填满屏幕在指令上设置 rotation: 90——内部 transformCoords() 会将触摸坐标 (clientX, clientY) 映射为 (clientY, -clientX)，从而使滚动方向与旋转后的表格逻辑轴对齐","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"122":{"title":"配置说明","content":"rotation 参数支持以下值： 值说明0不旋转（默认值）90容器顺时针旋转 90°-90容器逆时针旋转 90°180容器旋转 180°","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"123":{"title":"在线演示","content":"此示例需要在移动端设备中体验。点击按钮即可进入全屏横屏模式。","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"124":{"title":"旋转定位原理","content":"transform-origin: top left 配合 translate: 100vw 0 是关键的定位技巧。绕左上角顺时针旋转 90° 后，容器会偏移到屏幕左侧之外，而 translate: 100vw 0 将其推回，使其刚好覆盖整个视口。","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"125":{"title":"注意事项","content":"","titles":["移动端横屏方案"]},"126":{"title":"横屏时建议关闭边缘检测","content":"横屏模式下，建议将 disableEdgeDetection 设为 true。主要原因是：在横向浏览宽表时，手势经常会滑到屏幕边缘；如果继续保留边缘检测，手势可能在边缘被释放并触发系统原生事件（例如返回手势）。关闭边缘检测后，边缘滑动会继续由表格滚动逻辑接管，避免误触发系统级操作。 如果你是通过状态切换横屏，也可以显式写成：","titles":["移动端横屏方案","注意事项"]},"127":{"title":"安全区域适配","content":"在带有刘海屏或圆角的设备（如 iPhone）上，建议将安全区应用到横屏容器本身：","titles":["移动端横屏方案","注意事项"]},"128":{"title":"响应式尺寸","content":"当